## What I Learned

###  Ethical Hacking Fundamentals

* Difference between ethical hackers, black hat, and gray hat hackers
* Importance of authorization and legal boundaries
* Real-world purpose of penetration testing

###  Information Security Concepts

* Confidentiality, Integrity, Availability (CIA Triad)
* Risk, threat, vulnerability, and attack surface
* Security controls (preventive, detective, corrective)

###  Hacker Classes & Attack Phases

* Script kiddies, cyber criminals, insiders, hacktivists, nation-state actors
* Ethical hacking methodology:

  * Footprinting & reconnaissance
  * Scanning networks
  * Gaining access
  * Maintaining access
  * Clearing tracks

### Penetration Testing Basics

* Black-box, white-box, and gray-box testing
* Rules of engagement
* Reporting and documentation

### Key Skills Introduced

* Critical thinking and problem-solving mindset
* Understanding security from an attackerâ€™s perspective
* Responsible disclosure principles

